  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law in the United States, money laundering can result in serious criminal penalties:\n\n1. Potential Penalties:\n- Imprisonment: Up to 20 years per offense\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Forfeiture of assets involved in the laundering\n- Criminal record\n\n2. Specific Statute (18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1956):\n- Penalties can include up to 20 years in prison\n- Fines up to $500,000 or twice the value of property involved\n\n3. Additional Consequences:\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n\nThe exact penalties depend on specific circumstances, amount of money involved, and individual case details. Consulting a legal professional would provide the most accurate information for a specific situation.",
